Sentencas: One key issue in the application of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) is to develop novel cathode materials with excellent electrochemical performance and outstanding CO, tolerance ability.
Titulo: Advanced Electrochemical Performance and CO2 Tolerance of Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe1-xTixO3-δ Perovskite Materials as Oxygen Reduction Cathodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In the present study, perovskite-type materials Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe1-xTixO3-delta (BSFTx, x = 0.05-0.20) are evaluated as possible Fe-based cathode candidates for SOFCs.
Titulo: Advanced Electrochemical Performance and CO2 Tolerance of Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe1-xTixO3-δ Perovskite Materials as Oxygen Reduction Cathodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The phase structure, thermal expansion property, and electrocatalytic properties of BSFTx cathodes are systematically studied.
Titulo: Advanced Electrochemical Performance and CO2 Tolerance of Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe1-xTixO3-δ Perovskite Materials as Oxygen Reduction Cathodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The best oxygen reduction reaction activity is observed in the Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe1-xTixO3-delta (BSFT0.15) cathode.
Titulo: Advanced Electrochemical Performance and CO2 Tolerance of Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe1-xTixO3-δ Perovskite Materials as Oxygen Reduction Cathodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of the BSFT0.15 cathode is 0.085 Omega cm(2) and the peak power density of the cell with the BSFT0.15 cathode reaches to 1.41 W cm(-2) at 700 degrees
Titulo: Advanced Electrochemical Performance and CO2 Tolerance of Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe1-xTixO3-δ Perovskite Materials as Oxygen Reduction Cathodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: C. Moreover, the BSFT0.15 cathode exhibits good CO2 tolerance and chemical stability in a high concentration of CO2.
Titulo: Advanced Electrochemical Performance and CO2 Tolerance of Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe1-xTixO3-δ Perovskite Materials as Oxygen Reduction Cathodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The excellent CO2 tolerance property is associated with remarkable acidity of the Ti4+ cation and the large average bonding energy of BSFT0.15.
Titulo: Advanced Electrochemical Performance and CO2 Tolerance of Bi0.5Sr0.5Fe1-xTixO3-δ Perovskite Materials as Oxygen Reduction Cathodes for Intermediate-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
